First, you must brew a good espresso!
Then, grind 18g of coffee using a good burr grinder to a fine/espresso consistency.

After evenly
distributing the coffee
inside the
portafilter, tamp it.
Lock the portafilter into the espresso machine, and brew for 25-30 seconds aiming for a double shot (around 60ml of tasty espresso).
[b]Pro tip:[/b] Always check if your machine's water tank is filled. In case it's not, use good quality mineral water to refill it!
Ensure the milk stays below 65Â°C. This will help you achieve a smooth foam with tiny bubbles.
Now pour milk or a milk alternative into your pitcher and use the steam wand to create a whirlpool effect.
Feeling fancy? Give latte art a try!
Pour the steamed milk into the espresso cup holding back the foam, then pour the foam on top of everything.
